In [3]:
# Default function to fit a linear classifier and plot the decision boundary
def demo_clf(clf, X_train, y_train, name):
    
    clf.fit(X_train, y_train)
    risk_train = 1-clf.score(X_train, y_train)
    print('Training risk:', risk_train)

    plt.figure()
    sns.scatterplot(x=X_train['sepal_length'], y=X_train['sepal_width'],hue = y_train, style = y_train, markers=["o", "s"], legend=[])
    x0 = np.arange(4.5,7,.01)
    b0 = clf.intercept_
    b1 = clf.coef_[0,0]
    b2 = clf.coef_[0,1]
    plt.plot(x0, (-b0-b1*x0)/b2, color='red')
    plt.title(name)
    return risk_train

Comparison of LDA, Perceptron, Least-squares and Logistic regression¶

In [4]:
# Comparison of the different linear classifiers
print('LDA')
LDA_clf = LinearDiscriminantAnalysis()
demo_clf(LDA_clf, X, y, 'LDA')
if svfigs:
    plt.savefig(svdir + 'linearclfiris_' + 'LDA' + '.png')
    
print('Perceptron')
Perceptron_clf = linear_model.Perceptron(tol=1e-8, n_iter_no_change=500, max_iter = 10000)
demo_clf(Perceptron_clf, X, y, 'Perceptron')
if svfigs:
    plt.savefig(svdir + 'linearclfiris_' + 'Perceptron' + '.png')

print('Least-squares')
LS_clf = linear_model.RidgeClassifier(alpha=0) # OLS
demo_clf(LS_clf, X, y, 'Least-Squares')
if svfigs:
    plt.savefig(svdir + 'linearclfiris_' + 'LS' + '.png')

print('Logistic Regression')
logreg_clf = linear_model.LogisticRegression(penalty='none')
demo_clf(logreg_clf, X, y, 'Logistic Regression')
if svfigs:
    plt.savefig(svdir + 'linearclfiris_' + 'logreg' + '.png')

Multiclass classification on the Crabs dataset¶

In [6]:
# Load the crabs dataset
url = 'https://vincentarelbundock.github.io/Rdatasets/csv/MASS/crabs.csv'
crabs = pd.read_csv(url) # load it as a panda table
crabs['class'] = crabs['sp']+ crabs['sex']
crabs = crabs.drop(columns=['Unnamed: 0', 'sp', 'sex', 'index'])

# Data matrix X
X = crabs[['FL', 'RW', 'CL', 'CW', 'BD']]
# Class y (used later on to interpret the results of the PCA)
y = crabs['class']
In [7]:
# Project on two dimensions using LDA
LDA_clf = LinearDiscriminantAnalysis(n_components=2)
LDA_clf.fit(X, y)
Z = LDA_clf.transform(X)
crabs2 = pd.concat([pd.DataFrame(Z, columns = ['DC1', 'DC2']),y], axis=1)   

plt.figure()
sns.scatterplot(x=crabs2['DC1'], y=crabs2['DC2'], hue = crabs2['class'], markers=["o", "s", "D", "d"]);
plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.01, 1),borderaxespad=0)
if svfigs:
    plt.savefig(svdir + 'linearclf_crabs.png')
In [8]:
# Look at prediction over a grid of values
x1 = np.arange(-7, 7, 0.1)
x2 = np.arange(-6, 6, 0.1)
xx1, xx2 = np.meshgrid(x1, x2)
xtest = np.column_stack([xx1.reshape(-1,1), xx2.reshape(-1,1)])
In [9]:
color_dict = dict({'BM':sns.color_palette()[0],
                  'BF':sns.color_palette()[1],
                  'OM': sns.color_palette()[2],
                  'OF': sns.color_palette()[3]})

def plot_pred(xtest, ytest, title):
    plt.figure()
    sns.scatterplot(x=xtest[:,0], y=xtest[:,1], hue = ytest, legend = None, alpha=0.1, palette = color_dict)
    sns.scatterplot(x=crabs2['DC1'], y=crabs2['DC2'], palette = color_dict, hue = crabs2['class'], markers=["o", "s", "D", "d"]);
    plt.title(title)
    plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.01, 1),borderaxespad=0)
In [10]:
# LDA classifier (note that LDA is used on the 2D projections, not the whole data)
ytest = LDA_clf.fit(Z, y).predict(xtest)
plot_pred(xtest, ytest, 'LDA')
if svfigs:
    plt.savefig(svdir + 'linearclf_crabs_LDA.png')
